1
00:00:00,510 --> 00:00:02,969
<v Cop A>Huh? You found a hundred yen?

2
00:00:02,969 --> 00:00:05,290
<v Cop A>How old are you?

3
00:00:05,290 --> 00:00:06,230
<v Nao>What?

4
00:00:06,590 --> 00:00:10,380
<v Nao>Um, I'm eighteen. Why?

5
00:00:11,490 --> 00:00:12,990
<v sign>Tokyo Police
2nd District Police Station

6
00:00:13,280 --> 00:00:17,340
<v Cop B>Don't meet a lot of people 
that honest these days.

7
00:00:17,830 --> 00:00:22,330
<v sign>Nao Kanzaki

8
00:00:17,820 --> 00:00:20,750
<v Cop A>Stupidly honest, you might say.

9
00:00:22,580 --> 00:00:24,680
<v Nao>"Stupidly honest Nao."

10
00:00:24,680 --> 00:00:27,310
<v Nao>That's what people always called me.

11
00:00:28,090 --> 00:00:30,830
<v Nao>But I never let it bother me.

12
00:00:31,380 --> 00:00:35,320
<v Nao>After all, my father named me Nao

13
00:00:35,320 --> 00:00:37,840
<v Nao>because he wanted me 
to be an honest girl.

14
00:00:39,930 --> 00:00:41,740
<v Delivery>Package delivery.

15
00:00:45,250 --> 00:00:47,150
<v Nao>I don't remember ordering anything.

16
00:00:47,830 --> 00:00:51,690
<v Nao>The sender is... "LGT Office."

17
00:00:52,530 --> 00:00:53,530
<v Nao>What is this?

18
00:00:55,610 --> 00:01:07,290
<v sign>Ms. Nao Kanzaki, 
 Congratulations.
 You have beaten the 1-in-100, 000 odds
to participate in the Liar Game Tournament.

19
00:00:56,790 --> 00:01:01,880
<v Nao>"You have beaten the 1-in-100, 000 odds

20
00:01:01,880 --> 00:01:06,340
<v Nao>to participate in the 
Liar Game Tournament."

21
00:01:07,680 --> 00:01:08,830
<v Nao>Huh...

22
00:01:09,820 --> 00:01:12,130
<v Nao>Thinking back now, 

23
00:01:12,130 --> 00:01:16,800
<v Nao>I really should have thought a lot more 
carefully before opening that box.

24
00:01:20,230 --> 00:01:21,950
<v Nao>Th-This is...

25
00:01:25,020 --> 00:01:29,480
<v sign>The Legendary Con Artist

26
00:01:25,340 --> 00:01:29,480
<v Nao>Eighty, ninety, a hundred...

27
00:01:29,810 --> 00:01:32,150
<v Nao>A hundred million yen, and it's real!

28
00:01:33,640 --> 00:01:35,490
<v Nao>Wh-What's that?!

29
00:01:33,080 --> 00:01:35,490
<v Voice>If you are hearing this message, 

30
00:01:35,490 --> 00:01:40,240
<v Voice>it means that you are now an official 
participant in the Liar Game.

31
00:01:40,240 --> 00:01:42,310
<v Voice>This decision cannot be reversed.

32
00:01:42,690 --> 00:01:48,290
<v Voice>The enclosed 100 million yen is your 
game money for the first round.

33
00:01:48,960 --> 00:01:52,140
<v Nao>What in the world is the Liar Game?

34
00:01:53,250 --> 00:01:55,090
<v sign>100 Million Yen Battle

35
00:01:53,160 --> 00:01:55,090
<v Voice>The rules are simple.

36
00:01:55,090 --> 00:02:01,050
<v Voice>Take your opponent's game money
 by any means necessary.

37
00:02:01,050 --> 00:02:03,940
<v Voice>Participation in this game 
is by mutual consent.

38
00:02:03,940 --> 00:02:07,600
<v Voice>No actions taken in the theft of game 
money will be considered criminal.

39
00:02:08,110 --> 00:02:10,340
<v Voice>This is a one-on-one battle.

40
00:02:10,340 --> 00:02:15,210
<v Voice>The game begins the moment you are 
informed of your opponent's identity.

41
00:02:15,210 --> 00:02:18,710
<v Voice>The game will end thirty days thereafter.

42
00:02:18,710 --> 00:02:21,500
<v Voice>Whoever has more game money 
at that time will be the winner.

43
00:02:22,120 --> 00:02:23,610
<v Voice>Once the game is over, 

44
00:02:23,610 --> 00:02:26,650
<v Voice>a representative of the LGT Office
will come to collect the game money.

45
00:02:26,650 --> 00:02:31,860
<v Voice>The serial numbers of the 100 million yen
 must match those of your starting pool.

46
00:02:32,290 --> 00:02:35,820
<v Voice>Please return this to the 
representative on arrival.

47
00:02:35,820 --> 00:02:38,030
<v Voice>If you have stolen game 
money from your opponent, 

48
00:02:38,030 --> 00:02:40,630
<v Voice>you will be allowed to keep the excess.

49
00:02:40,630 --> 00:02:45,940
<v Voice>In other words, it is possible to win 
up to 100 million yen in this game.

50
00:02:45,940 --> 00:02:48,780
<v Voice>Conversely, if you have 
lost any game money, 

51
00:02:48,780 --> 00:02:52,640
<v Voice>you will be forced to pay the difference, 
even if that leaves you in debt.

52
00:02:53,450 --> 00:02:56,630
<v Nao>If I lose, I could end up 
100 million yen in debt?

53
00:02:58,090 --> 00:03:00,030
<v Nao>My mind was spinning.

54
00:03:00,330 --> 00:03:02,960
<v Nao>Not with dreams of the 
incredible money I could win, 

55
00:03:03,410 --> 00:03:07,300
<v Nao>but with the fear of ending up
 100 million yen in debt.

56
00:03:09,430 --> 00:03:13,910
<v Nao>What do I do? Who could I even talk to?

57
00:03:14,700 --> 00:03:16,680
<v Nao>The only family I had in the world...

58
00:03:18,850 --> 00:03:21,840
<v Nao>was fighting terminal cancer 
in a care facility.

59
00:03:22,440 --> 00:03:24,180
<v Nao>Hey, Dad. How are you feeling?

60
00:03:24,480 --> 00:03:28,180
<v Nao's Dad>Very well. Thanks to the 
lovely weather, I suppose.

61
00:03:28,530 --> 00:03:30,360
<v Nao>Oh, I'm glad.

62
00:03:30,360 --> 00:03:35,880
<v Nao>They said they weren't sure 
he'd make it to New Year's.

63
00:03:36,930 --> 00:03:41,940
<v Nao's Dad>Hey there. Is something bothering you?

64
00:03:41,940 --> 00:03:45,210
<v Nao>Huh? No, everything's going great!

65
00:03:45,510 --> 00:03:47,110
<v Nao>I'm even getting used to school.

66
00:03:47,110 --> 00:03:49,170
<v Nao>Every day is fun!

67
00:03:46,920 --> 00:03:49,170
<v Nao>My one trivial hope in this world...

68
00:03:49,960 --> 00:03:53,970
<v Nao>was to make my father's final days

69
00:03:53,970 --> 00:03:57,890
<v Nao>as peaceful and quiet as possible.

70
00:03:59,250 --> 00:04:02,430
<v Nao>I couldn't tell him.

71
00:04:03,470 --> 00:04:04,970
<v sign>Mitsuo Tanimura Law Office

72
00:04:04,970 --> 00:04:08,090
<v Tanimura>There's nothing you can do 
about this at the moment.

73
00:04:08,090 --> 00:04:08,820
<v Nao>What?!

74
00:04:08,820 --> 00:04:14,490
<v Tanimura>It's a lawyer's job to help people 
who've suffered some kind of damages.

75
00:04:14,490 --> 00:04:18,310
<v Tanimura>But you haven't suffered 
any damages, have you?

76
00:04:19,649 --> 00:04:22,010
<v Nao>If a lawyer can't help me...

77
00:04:22,880 --> 00:04:25,820
<v Nao>I know! If I take it to the police...

78
00:04:27,570 --> 00:04:31,090
<v Tanimura>That's probably exactly 
what the sender wants.

79
00:04:31,090 --> 00:04:31,900
<v Nao>What?!

80
00:04:31,900 --> 00:04:38,480
<v Tanimura>I mean, wouldn't most folks go to the cops
 rather than risk winding up in trouble?

81
00:04:38,480 --> 00:04:39,510
<v Nao>Yes!

82
00:04:39,510 --> 00:04:42,780
<v Tanimura>But it says right here in the rules

83
00:04:42,780 --> 00:04:45,390
<v Tanimura>that the player must return the game money

84
00:04:45,390 --> 00:04:49,040
<v Tanimura>to the representative on arrival.

85
00:04:49,040 --> 00:04:54,350
<v Tanimura>But if you take it to the police, 
they'll treat it like a lost article.

86
00:04:54,350 --> 00:04:56,490
<v Tanimura>That's the trap!

87
00:04:56,770 --> 00:04:58,740
<v Tanimura>When it comes time to collect

88
00:04:58,740 --> 00:05:01,660
<v Tanimura>and you tell 'em, "The owner is back, 
so please return the money, "

89
00:05:01,660 --> 00:05:03,980
<v Tanimura>you think the police will give it to you?

90
00:05:05,210 --> 00:05:09,690
<v Tanimura>Police only return lost articles 
to whoever lost them.

91
00:05:10,250 --> 00:05:16,070
<v Tanimura>So when the office shows up as the owner
and claims that money from the police, 

92
00:05:16,070 --> 00:05:19,740
<v Tanimura>they're gonna say you owe them 100 mil!

93
00:05:20,140 --> 00:05:23,750
<v Nao>That's awful... This is like a scam.

94
00:05:23,750 --> 00:05:25,630
<v Nao>Isn't there anything I can do?

95
00:05:26,420 --> 00:05:29,760
<v Tanimura>Nothing at this point, like I said.

96
00:05:30,330 --> 00:05:33,420
<v Nao>Then who should I talk to?

97
00:05:33,420 --> 00:05:37,820
<v Tanimura>For advice on a con, 
it's best to talk to a con artist.

98
00:05:38,320 --> 00:05:41,070
<v Nao>Isn't there anything 
more useful you can—

99
00:05:41,070 --> 00:05:43,270
<v Tanimura>Well, that's your hour up.

100
00:05:43,750 --> 00:05:47,930
<v Tanimura>Moving forward, 
it'll be 15, 000 yen an hour.

101
00:05:47,930 --> 00:05:49,530
<v Tanimura>What do you say?

102
00:05:53,590 --> 00:05:56,540
<v Nao>What in the world is the Liar Game?

103
00:05:58,330 --> 00:06:00,710
<v Nao>Why would they do this to people?

104
00:06:01,510 --> 00:06:03,410
<v Nao>Why would they choose me?

105
00:06:24,230 --> 00:06:28,050
<v Nao>"Your opponent for the first round 
of the Liar Game has been selected."

106
00:06:28,720 --> 00:06:32,030
<v Nao>"Your opponent is the player enclosed."

107
00:06:33,410 --> 00:06:34,660
<v Nao>I know this man!

108
00:06:35,010 --> 00:06:36,760
<v Nao>That's Fujisawa-sensei!

109
00:06:39,180 --> 00:06:40,670
<v Nao>What a shock.

110
00:06:41,160 --> 00:06:43,590
<v Nao>He was my homeroom teacher 
in middle school.

111
00:06:43,590 --> 00:06:47,200
<v Nao>He helped me when my dad got sick and 
with deciding what high school to attend.

112
00:06:47,200 --> 00:06:49,160
<v Nao>He's such a kind teacher...

113
00:06:50,530 --> 00:06:52,210
<v Nao>I can work with him!

114
00:06:52,670 --> 00:06:54,950
<v Fujisawa>Talk about a lucky break.

115
00:06:54,950 --> 00:06:57,550
<v Fujisawa>Never thought you'd be my opponent!

116
00:06:57,550 --> 00:06:59,000
<v Nao>I feel the same!

117
00:06:59,450 --> 00:07:01,350
<v Fujisawa>By the way, Kanzaki-kun...

118
00:07:01,760 --> 00:07:06,040
<v Fujisawa>You don't honestly think this 
is a real game where people

119
00:07:06,040 --> 00:07:10,150
<v Fujisawa>are chosen at random to 
play for money, do you?

120
00:07:10,150 --> 00:07:11,800
<v Nao>You don't think it is?

121
00:07:11,800 --> 00:07:13,690
<v Fujisawa>Absolutely not.

122
00:07:14,370 --> 00:07:19,790
<v Fujisawa>This is a sham game that 
neither player can ever win.

123
00:07:19,790 --> 00:07:21,200
<v Nao>What?!

124
00:07:21,410 --> 00:07:25,840
<v Fujisawa>Let's say you were up 
against a complete stranger.

125
00:07:25,840 --> 00:07:30,350
<v Fujisawa>If the 100 million went missing 
while you were asleep, 

126
00:07:30,350 --> 00:07:32,880
<v Fujisawa>you'd assume he took it, right?

127
00:07:33,500 --> 00:07:34,730
<v Nao>Yes.

128
00:07:34,730 --> 00:07:40,360
<v Fujisawa>But what if it was the Liar Game 
Tournament Office that took it?

129
00:07:41,850 --> 00:07:46,600
<v Fujisawa>They easily could. They have the names 
and home addresses of all the players.

130
00:07:46,880 --> 00:07:51,380
<v Fujisawa>But each player would assume
that their opponent was the culprit.

131
00:07:51,730 --> 00:07:57,380
<v Fujisawa>Then, when the game is over, 
they're both 100 million in debt.

132
00:07:58,290 --> 00:07:59,720
<v Nao>That's horrible.

133
00:07:59,720 --> 00:08:04,630
<v Nao>If not for you, I definitely would 
have fallen for their trick.

134
00:08:05,550 --> 00:08:09,700
<v Fujisawa>Now that you see that, let's 
move the money somewhere safe!

135
00:08:10,240 --> 00:08:15,880
<v Fujisawa>The executive office could be
 going after yours as we speak!

136
00:08:17,740 --> 00:08:18,640
<v Nao>It's still here!

137
00:08:19,110 --> 00:08:20,840
<v Nao>Thank goodness.

138
00:08:20,260 --> 00:08:23,270
<v Fujisawa>Looks like they haven't made 
their move just yet.

139
00:08:23,270 --> 00:08:26,400
<v Nao>Sensei, what should I do with it?

140
00:08:27,180 --> 00:08:30,540
<v Fujisawa>The smartest thing would 
be to store it with mine

141
00:08:30,540 --> 00:08:34,460
<v Fujisawa>in a safe deposit box at the 
bank until the game is over.

142
00:08:34,460 --> 00:08:36,169
<v Nao>Great idea!

143
00:08:36,169 --> 00:08:38,840
<v Fujisawa>I'll make the arrangements.

144
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:42,179
<v Fujisawa>I'll accept full responsibility 
for ensuring the money's safety.

145
00:08:42,860 --> 00:08:44,250
<v Nao>Please take care of it.

146
00:08:55,430 --> 00:08:58,290
<v Nao>At last, I can get a good night's sleep.

147
00:09:05,110 --> 00:09:08,890
<v Nao>How long was I out?

148
00:09:14,500 --> 00:09:15,590
<v Nao>What is this?

149
00:09:17,100 --> 00:09:19,780
<v Nao>"Liar Game Progress Report."

150
00:09:16,280 --> 00:09:23,160
<v sign>Progress Report

151
00:09:16,280 --> 00:09:23,160
<v sign>Kazuo Fujisawa

152
00:09:16,280 --> 00:09:23,160
<v sign>Nao Kanzaki

153
00:09:16,280 --> 00:09:23,160
<v sign>You are currently losing. The game will end in 29 days.

154
00:09:20,320 --> 00:09:22,680
<v Nao>"You are currently losing."

155
00:09:24,490 --> 00:09:26,000
<v Nao>What in the world?

156
00:09:26,900 --> 00:09:30,540
<v Fujisawa>Oh, so that's their play, is it?

157
00:09:31,100 --> 00:09:35,540
<v Fujisawa>I suspect they've realized 
we know each other.

158
00:09:35,540 --> 00:09:39,290
<v Fujisawa>They can't scam us if we work together, 

159
00:09:39,830 --> 00:09:43,630
<v Fujisawa>so they sent you that card 
to sow distrust.

160
00:09:44,190 --> 00:09:45,690
<v Nao>I see.

161
00:09:46,690 --> 00:09:50,430
<v Nao>But of course I still trust you, Sensei!

162
00:09:50,430 --> 00:09:52,230
<v Fujisawa>I know that, dear.

163
00:09:52,440 --> 00:09:54,730
<v sign>Fujisawa-sensei

164
00:09:54,970 --> 00:09:57,420
<v Nao>I feel so silly for saying that...

165
00:09:58,190 --> 00:09:59,560
<v Nao>I know!

166
00:10:00,150 --> 00:10:03,500
<v Nao>I'll go to his house 
and apologize in person.

167
00:10:06,820 --> 00:10:10,610
<v Fujisawa>Yeah, that's right! A hundred million!

168
00:10:10,610 --> 00:10:12,680
<v Fujisawa>Enough to pay off my debts in one go!

169
00:10:12,680 --> 00:10:14,730
<v Nao>Is he talking about the Liar Game?

170
00:10:15,460 --> 00:10:21,380
<v Fujisawa>My opponent? One of my students 
from five years ago!

171
00:10:21,380 --> 00:10:24,230
<v Fujisawa>She's as honest as they come.

172
00:10:24,230 --> 00:10:26,730
<v Fujisawa>She bought it hook, line, and sinker.

173
00:10:26,730 --> 00:10:29,720
<v Fujisawa>She doesn't even realize
 I stole her hundred million!

174
00:10:31,290 --> 00:10:33,890
<v Fujisawa>She's stupidly honest.

175
00:10:45,330 --> 00:10:46,830
<v sign>Progress Report

176
00:10:45,330 --> 00:10:46,830
<v sign>Kazuo Fujisawa

177
00:10:45,330 --> 00:10:46,830
<v sign>Nao Kanzaki

178
00:10:45,330 --> 00:10:46,830
<v sign>You are currently losing. The game will end in 29 days.

179
00:10:47,770 --> 00:10:49,030
<v Nao>"Liar"?

180
00:10:50,500 --> 00:10:51,720
<v Nao>One who lies...

181
00:10:53,610 --> 00:10:54,520
<v Nao>It can't be!

182
00:10:55,710 --> 00:10:58,730
<v Nao>That's it. He...

183
00:11:00,600 --> 00:11:02,220
<v Nao>He tricked me!

184
00:11:12,250 --> 00:11:16,420
<v Nao>At last, I realized what had happened.

185
00:11:24,390 --> 00:11:26,060
<v Nao>I have to get it back...

186
00:11:27,210 --> 00:11:31,080
<v Nao>I have to get that 100 million back!

187
00:11:32,950 --> 00:11:37,370
<v Nao>For advice on a con, 
it's best to talk to a con artist.

188
00:11:38,410 --> 00:11:40,100
<v Nao>A con artist...

189
00:11:47,010 --> 00:11:48,580
<v sign>The Latest on Massive Scam
Genius Con Artist to Be Released Soon

190
00:11:48,580 --> 00:11:50,020
<v sign>The Latest on Massive Scam
Genius Con Artist to Be Released Soon

191
00:11:50,200 --> 00:11:52,250
<v sign>Genius Con Artist to Be Released Soon

192
00:11:51,040 --> 00:11:54,020
<v Nao>The genius con artist

193
00:11:54,520 --> 00:11:58,380
<v Nao>who took down the corrupt business
 network Shuei Corporation, 

194
00:11:58,380 --> 00:12:03,340
<v Nao>Shinichi Akiyama, 
will soon complete his sentence.

195
00:12:00,530 --> 00:12:05,030
<v sign>Shinichi Akiyama, soon to be released

196
00:12:06,030 --> 00:12:07,540
<v Reporter A>Should be just about time.

197
00:12:10,040 --> 00:12:10,850
<v Reporter B>That him?

198
00:12:11,400 --> 00:12:14,600
<v Reporter C>No, it's a different convict.

199
00:12:16,770 --> 00:12:18,310
<v Guard A>Excuse us.

200
00:12:19,230 --> 00:12:22,170
<v Guard A>Could we ask you to get going?

201
00:12:22,170 --> 00:12:24,270
<v Reporter A>Where's Akiyama?

202
00:12:24,270 --> 00:12:25,750
<v Guard B (Akiyama)>He's been released.

203
00:12:25,750 --> 00:12:27,690
<v Reporter B>But that wasn't him.

204
00:12:27,970 --> 00:12:31,550
<v Guard B (Akiyama)>Akiyama is a master of disguise, you know.

205
00:12:33,310 --> 00:12:34,510
<v Reporter A>He tricked us!

206
00:12:34,510 --> 00:12:36,830
<v Reporter B>After him! We can still make it!

207
00:12:40,510 --> 00:12:44,700
<v Guard A>Nice work driving them off, Akiyama.

208
00:12:47,130 --> 00:12:48,620
<v Nao>What will I do?!

209
00:12:49,330 --> 00:12:50,990
<v Nao>Where's the way in?

210
00:12:50,990 --> 00:12:53,160
<v Nao>How could I get lost now, of all times?

211
00:12:56,950 --> 00:12:58,890
<v Nao>Ow...

212
00:13:00,120 --> 00:13:02,140
<v Nao>I-I'm so sorry.

213
00:13:02,570 --> 00:13:03,370
<v Nao>Um...

214
00:13:06,700 --> 00:13:08,520
<v Nao>Are you Akiyama-san?!

215
00:13:11,330 --> 00:13:13,030
<v Akiyama>You've got the wrong guy.

216
00:13:13,030 --> 00:13:14,420
<v Nao>Wait!

217
00:13:15,510 --> 00:13:18,760
<v Nao>Please, help me!

218
00:13:19,270 --> 00:13:22,990
<v Nao>I was betrayed by someone I trusted.

219
00:13:24,470 --> 00:13:27,760
<v Nao>He took 100 million yen from me.

220
00:13:30,580 --> 00:13:33,680
<v Akiyama>There's nothing I can do to help you.

221
00:13:34,480 --> 00:13:37,230
<v Akiyama>Talk to the cops or a lawyer or something.

222
00:13:37,790 --> 00:13:39,090
<v Nao>I can't!

223
00:13:39,520 --> 00:13:42,410
<v Nao>You're the only person who can help me!

224
00:13:44,910 --> 00:13:48,970
<v Akiyama>Do you realize what you're saying?

225
00:13:49,800 --> 00:13:52,620
<v Akiyama>You're asking a man 
who just got out of prison

226
00:13:52,620 --> 00:13:55,260
<v Akiyama>to help you steal 100 million yen.

227
00:13:55,800 --> 00:14:00,020
<v Akiyama>Even if someone scammed you out of it, 
stealing that money back is theft.

228
00:14:00,860 --> 00:14:05,050
<v Akiyama>You're asking me to get 
myself arrested again!

229
00:14:06,120 --> 00:14:07,590
<v Nao>Well...

230
00:14:28,130 --> 00:14:30,470
<v Akiyama>How long are you going to follow me?

231
00:14:30,470 --> 00:14:33,600
<v Nao>Until you hear me out.

232
00:14:35,440 --> 00:14:38,980
<v Akiyama>Fine. I'll listen to your story, at least.

233
00:14:39,600 --> 00:14:42,840
<v Akiyama>I'm going to drop my stuff off
 at my place, so just wait there.

234
00:14:43,260 --> 00:14:44,800
<v Akiyama>Wait right there.

235
00:14:45,490 --> 00:14:46,540
<v Nao>Okay!

236
00:14:47,230 --> 00:14:51,470
<v sign>Izakaya Yocchan
Japanese Sake, 
 Shochu, Craft Beer

237
00:14:54,250 --> 00:14:55,770
<v Bartender>Thanks for coming.

238
00:14:57,180 --> 00:14:59,580
<v Nao>He's been gone a while...

239
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:03,550
<v Akiyama>She's still waiting?

240
00:15:04,790 --> 00:15:07,000
<v sign>Izakaya Yocchan

241
00:15:05,410 --> 00:15:07,000
<v Punk A>Hey!

242
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:09,260
<v Punk A>Let's have some fun, girlie.

243
00:15:09,260 --> 00:15:11,660
<v Nao>I'm waiting for someone.

244
00:15:11,660 --> 00:15:14,020
<v Punk A>Come on. You've been here for hours.

245
00:15:14,020 --> 00:15:19,220
<v Punk B>I think you're looking for a man 
who'll really rock your world—

246
00:15:19,580 --> 00:15:21,160
<v Nao>Akiyama-san!

247
00:15:21,160 --> 00:15:22,970
<v Akiyama>Sorry for the long wait.

248
00:15:23,220 --> 00:15:24,290
<v Akiyama>Let's go.

249
00:15:24,700 --> 00:15:25,610
<v Nao>Okay!

250
00:15:26,610 --> 00:15:28,610
<v sign>Strawberry au Lait

251
00:15:26,610 --> 00:15:28,610
<v sign>Umeboshi Rice Ball

252
00:15:26,610 --> 00:15:28,610
<v sign>Coarse Red Bean Bun

253
00:15:30,130 --> 00:15:31,790
<v Akiyama>You can really pack it in.

254
00:15:33,270 --> 00:15:36,330
<v Nao>I didn't have anything to eat 
the whole time I was waiting.

255
00:15:36,820 --> 00:15:39,670
<v Akiyama>Why the hell not? You could've passed out.

256
00:15:39,670 --> 00:15:42,880
<v Nao>But you told me to wait right there...

257
00:15:43,980 --> 00:15:49,150
<v Akiyama>Seriously? Most people would get
 the hint after a couple of hours.

258
00:15:49,150 --> 00:15:51,500
<v Nao>Huh? What did you just say?

259
00:15:53,530 --> 00:15:56,880
<v Akiyama>You're stupidly honest. 
This is why you got scammed.

260
00:16:00,340 --> 00:16:03,590
<v Nao>Is it wrong to be stupidly honest?

261
00:16:06,500 --> 00:16:09,420
<v Akiyama>Tell me about your 100 million.

262
00:16:12,050 --> 00:16:14,210
<v Akiyama>The Liar Game, huh?

263
00:16:14,210 --> 00:16:17,170
<v Akiyama>Seems hard to believe, but...

264
00:16:17,970 --> 00:16:19,700
<v Akiyama>What do you want to do?

265
00:16:20,290 --> 00:16:22,140
<v Akiyama>Win the game?

266
00:16:22,140 --> 00:16:25,360
<v Akiyama>Or wash your hands of the 
whole shady business?

267
00:16:26,490 --> 00:16:28,020
<v Nao>I want out!

268
00:16:28,020 --> 00:16:31,730
<v Nao>I just want to get back my 
100 million and call it a day!

269
00:16:32,310 --> 00:16:34,300
<v Akiyama>That's simple, then.

270
00:16:34,300 --> 00:16:38,910
<v Akiyama>We'll tell your teacher how you feel 
and get him to return your money.

271
00:16:42,810 --> 00:16:46,250
<v Fujisawa>Hey, Kanzaki-kun. Who's that with you?

272
00:16:46,840 --> 00:16:48,070
<v Nao>Sensei...

273
00:16:48,480 --> 00:16:52,710
<v Nao>Will you please return 
my 100 million now?

274
00:16:53,440 --> 00:16:55,560
<v Fujisawa>Where's this coming from?

275
00:16:55,560 --> 00:16:59,030
<v Fujisawa>I told you, it's in a safe at the bank.

276
00:16:59,030 --> 00:17:02,940
<v Fujisawa>The safe can only be accessed 
during the bank's business hours.

277
00:17:02,940 --> 00:17:07,950
<v Fujisawa>And for your safety, it's best to 
keep it there until the game's over.

278
00:17:08,380 --> 00:17:11,150
<v Nao>I overheard you...

279
00:17:11,150 --> 00:17:13,839
<v Nao>What you said on the telephone.

280
00:17:14,470 --> 00:17:18,630
<v Nao>That you'd scammed 100 million 
yen from a student.

281
00:17:19,040 --> 00:17:22,680
<v Fujisawa>D-Don't know what you're talking about!

282
00:17:22,680 --> 00:17:24,819
<v Akiyama>I'll keep this brief.

283
00:17:25,530 --> 00:17:27,950
<v Akiyama>Return her 100 million.

284
00:17:28,470 --> 00:17:32,610
<v Akiyama>Do it by tomorrow, or we're 
taking you to the police.

285
00:17:32,610 --> 00:17:34,540
<v Fujisawa>Th-The police?!

286
00:17:34,540 --> 00:17:37,490
<v Fujisawa>This is just a game! 
It's there in the rules!

287
00:17:37,490 --> 00:17:40,360
<v Fujisawa>Any game money taken 
isn't considered a crime!

288
00:17:40,890 --> 00:17:44,120
<v Akiyama>So you acknowledge that this is a game?

289
00:17:45,630 --> 00:17:48,870
<v Akiyama>You see all of this as a game.

290
00:17:48,870 --> 00:17:52,510
<v Akiyama>Which is why you tricked her 
and took her 100 million.

291
00:18:01,380 --> 00:18:04,160
<v Fujisawa>That's right! I tricked her!

292
00:18:04,160 --> 00:18:07,040
<v Fujisawa>But you're in no position 
to criticize me for it!

293
00:18:07,040 --> 00:18:09,890
<v Fujisawa>Because this is all just a game!

294
00:18:09,890 --> 00:18:15,150
<v Fujisawa>If I hadn't taken her 100 million, 
she might have taken mine!

295
00:18:15,150 --> 00:18:17,410
<v Nao>I would never do that!

296
00:18:17,810 --> 00:18:23,050
<v Fujisawa>I don't believe you. 
People just aren't trustworthy.

297
00:18:23,740 --> 00:18:28,510
<v Fujisawa>I was in charge of class trips
 at my old school.

298
00:18:28,920 --> 00:18:33,270
<v Fujisawa>Every year, I booked with 
the same travel agency, 

299
00:18:33,270 --> 00:18:38,540
<v Fujisawa>and the head of the agency paid me 
a small kickback as a thank-you.

300
00:18:38,920 --> 00:18:44,170
<v Fujisawa>But one year, they said they 
weren't going to pay me.

301
00:18:44,170 --> 00:18:47,730
<v Fujisawa>And when I said I'd use another agency, 

302
00:18:47,730 --> 00:18:52,390
<v Fujisawa>the bastards snitched on me 
to the board of education!

303
00:18:54,440 --> 00:18:56,940
<v Fujisawa>I was fired on the spot.

304
00:18:57,330 --> 00:19:00,690
<v Fujisawa>My family left me.

305
00:19:00,690 --> 00:19:03,350
<v Fujisawa>That's just what people do!

306
00:19:03,350 --> 00:19:05,700
<v Fujisawa>When you trust them, 
 they make a fool of you!

307
00:19:05,700 --> 00:19:08,660
<v Fujisawa>But then I got the message 
about the Liar Game.

308
00:19:08,660 --> 00:19:12,700
<v Fujisawa>"I'm saved. There really 
is a God, " I thought.

309
00:19:12,700 --> 00:19:17,080
<v Fujisawa>So I have to win this game!

310
00:19:17,080 --> 00:19:20,470
<v Nao>Don't say that! Please help me, Sensei!

311
00:19:20,470 --> 00:19:22,620
<v Nao>My father has terminal cancer.

312
00:19:22,620 --> 00:19:27,010
<v Nao>I just want to make sure
 his final days are peaceful.

313
00:19:27,580 --> 00:19:31,720
<v Nao>If I end up 100 million in debt now...

314
00:19:31,720 --> 00:19:33,970
<v Fujisawa>I don't give a damn!

315
00:19:33,970 --> 00:19:37,200
<v Fujisawa>I don't give a damn about your dad!

316
00:19:37,200 --> 00:19:41,410
<v Fujisawa>I don't give a damn 
about anyone but myself!

317
00:19:42,250 --> 00:19:47,490
<v Fujisawa>Well, good luck thinking of a way
 to get the 100 million back.

318
00:19:52,500 --> 00:19:55,860
<v Akiyama>Hard to believe he was ever a teacher.

319
00:19:57,160 --> 00:19:59,730
<v Akiyama>Money really changes people.

320
00:19:59,730 --> 00:20:02,580
<v Akiyama>I've seen more than my share
 of that in the past.

321
00:20:05,610 --> 00:20:08,030
<v Akiyama>Crying won't get you out of this.

322
00:20:08,740 --> 00:20:15,510
<v Nao>A teacher I trusted put me
100 million yen in debt!

323
00:20:16,190 --> 00:20:19,480
<v Akiyama>You're not actually in debt yet.

324
00:20:19,930 --> 00:20:23,650
<v Nao>But the money's stowed 
in a safe deposit box.

325
00:20:24,160 --> 00:20:25,710
<v Akiyama>A safe deposit box...

326
00:20:26,190 --> 00:20:30,700
<v Akiyama>Ironically, Fujisawa just 
exposed his own weakness.

327
00:20:32,010 --> 00:20:33,410
<v Nao>His weakness?

328
00:20:34,440 --> 00:20:39,280
<v Akiyama>Safe deposit boxes can only be
 accessed when the bank is open.

329
00:20:40,370 --> 00:20:42,670
<v Akiyama>How long does the game last?

330
00:20:43,450 --> 00:20:45,950
<v Nao>There's 23 days left.

331
00:20:45,950 --> 00:20:50,120
<v Nao>So it ends on June 14th... A Sunday.

332
00:20:46,930 --> 00:20:50,930
<v sign>Game Ends

333
00:20:52,670 --> 00:20:55,540
<v Akiyama>No one's getting into the safe that day.

334
00:20:56,440 --> 00:21:01,720
<v Nao>He'd have to take the money 
out by 5:00 that Friday.

335
00:21:02,290 --> 00:21:06,950
<v Nao>Which means it'll be out of the safe 
for two days before the deadline!

336
00:21:07,650 --> 00:21:10,070
<v Akiyama>In other words, this isn't over yet.

337
00:21:11,570 --> 00:21:17,410
<v Nao>But even once the money's out of the safe, 
it won't be easy to steal, will it?

338
00:21:17,720 --> 00:21:20,780
<v Akiyama>Don't worry. I have a plan.

339
00:21:21,160 --> 00:21:22,750
<v Nao>Really?!

340
00:21:22,750 --> 00:21:25,380
<v Nao>Wait, does that mean...

341
00:21:26,220 --> 00:21:30,670
<v Nao>Akiyama-san, you're going to help me?!

342
00:21:31,390 --> 00:21:35,840
<v Akiyama>I refuse to be an accomplice to a crime, 

343
00:21:35,840 --> 00:21:39,110
<v Akiyama>but Fujisawa admitted 
that this was just a game.

344
00:21:40,250 --> 00:21:46,110
<v Akiyama>If it's just a game, and you're ready to
do what it takes to steal his 100 million, 

345
00:21:46,800 --> 00:21:48,260
<v Akiyama>I'm happy to help you.

346
00:21:50,390 --> 00:21:53,030
<v Nao>I am ready.

347
00:21:54,940 --> 00:21:56,990
<v Akiyama>I don't work cheap.

348
00:21:56,990 --> 00:21:58,640
<v Akiyama>We split your gains evenly.

349
00:21:58,640 --> 00:22:02,240
<v Akiyama>Meaning if we steal the whole pot, 
 I expect 50 million.

350
00:22:04,290 --> 00:22:07,410
<v Nao>Thank you so much! It's a deal!

351
00:22:07,410 --> 00:22:09,240
<v Akiyama>Keep your voice down, stupid.

352
00:23:45,060 --> 00:23:50,140
<v Sign>Next Time

353
00:23:45,060 --> 00:23:50,140
<v Sign>Shockwave
